Firefighters raced to save burning buildings and debris littered in the streets of Pretoria's CBD after a protest descended into a looting spree on Wednesday. It followed a shutdown earlier in the morning in which thousands of taxis blocked several roads. The protest soon turned violent and police used rubber bullets to stop looters who targeted various businesses. According to the City of Tshwane, the riots were incited by a shooting which resulted in the death of a taxi driver. WATCH | Police fire rubber bullets as looters run amok in Pretoria CBD Police fired rubber bullets and stun grenades after protesters started looting shops and setting buildings alight in the Pretoria CBD on Wednesday.

